<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 19 at 2:21AM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Van Buren
and southern Kalamazoo Counties through 315 AM EDT...
At 221 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hartford, or 10 miles north of Dowagiac, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Paw Paw...
Vicksburg...           Hartford...            Mattawan...
Lawton...              Decatur...             Schoolcraft...
Climax...              Kalamazoo-Battle Cre...
Fulton...
Keeler...              Lawrence...            Scotts...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
